    "en": {
      "title": "6.26 million people are severely food insecure",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the World Food Program in its report, 6.26 million people are food insecure in Sri Lanka.",
        "They pointed out that the people of Sri Lanka are facing the burden of food crisis in the economic crisis that Sri Lanka is facing and three out of ten families are found to be food insecure.",
        "Out of the 6.2 million people affected, 65,600 people face severe food insecurity, and Sri Lanka's food inflation in June 2022 was 57.4 percent.",
        "According to the World Food Programme, rising food prices have adversely affected people's ability to obtain enough nutritious food.",
        "Pointing out that two out of five families do not eat enough food, and the food security situation in the highlands is very bad, they have mentioned in their new report that more than half of the households in the highlands are in a state of food insecurity."
      ],
